============================================================
Manual live E2E verification (real dist/index.js, fresh temp HOME, fresh evidence
this session — real blockrun.ai gateway, not mocked)
============================================================

$ HOME=<tmp> node dist/index.js wallet --action deposit --json
  -> {"chain":"base","address":"0xAeCA5...","note":"Coinbase card top-up link:
     https://pay.coinbase.com/buy/select-asset?sessionToken=...&defaultAsset=USDC&
     defaultNetwork=base&fiatCurrency=USD\n...","url":"https://pay.coinbase.com/buy/
     select-asset?sessionToken=...","opened":false}
  -> exit 0. A REAL, freshly-minted one-time Coinbase Onramp URL.

$ curl -sI -o /dev/null -w "%{http_code}\n" "<the minted URL above>"
  -> 302 (a real, resolvable redirect from pay.coinbase.com — proves the link is
     genuine, not just well-formed-looking; no purchase flow was completed).

$ HOME=<tmp> node dist/index.js wallet --action chain --chain solana --json
  HOME=<tmp> node dist/index.js wallet --action deposit --json
  -> {"chain":"solana","address":"HnLUFK...","note":"Card top-up (Coinbase Onramp)
     is Base-only. To fund on Solana, run blockrun wallet --action setup for your
     address + QR (send USDC SPL), or switch with --action chain --chain base."}
  -> exit 0, no `url`/`opened` fields — payOnce() correctly never attempted.

$ HOME=<tmp> node dist/index.js wallet --action deposit --open --json
  -> {"chain":"base",...,"opened":true} exit 0 — --open successfully invoked
     openUrl() (this Mac's real `open` command) with no crash.

$ ls <tmp>/.blockrun/cli-budget.json
  -> does not exist at all after 4 deposit-only invocations above — deposit never
     writes to the persisted ledger (REQ-FUND-017's live money-safety proof; a
     ledger file that was never even CREATED is the strongest form of "spent/calls
     unchanged," since there is nothing to have changed).

